f the US, is Edward's great-great-great grandson."]}]},{"name":"Madam","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: The Scripture name, in Hebrew, Adham, signifying 'man;' literally earthy, red earth; Rudolph, however, says the name in Ethiopic means ' to be fair, beautiful.' Hence the nurse-name Addy, little Adam."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Madam Bluett was born about 1125, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Richard Bluett."},"et":{"Abt 1125–Deceased":"umbes 1125–Surnud","1121–Male":"1121–Surnud","1147–Female":"1147–Surnud","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1125":"1125","1147":"1147","1121":"1121","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","Helstan, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1125–Deceased":"noin 1125–Kuollut","1121–Male":"1121–Kuollut","1147–Female":"1147–Kuollut","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1125":"1125","1147":"1147","1121":"1121","Abt 1125":"noin 1125","Helstan, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1125–Deceased":"environ 1125–Décédée","1121–Male":"1121–Décédé","1147–Female":"1147–Décédée","1125–Female":"1125–Décédée","1125":"1125","1147":"1147","1121":"1121","Abt 1125":"environ 1125","Helstan, Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Madam Bluett est née environ 1125, à Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Richard Bluett."},"de":{"Abt 1125–Deceased":"um 1125–Verstorben","1121–Male":"1121–Verstorben","1147–Female":"1147–Verstorben","1125–Female":"1125–Verstorben","1125":"1125","1147":"1147","1121":"1121","Abt 1125":"um 1125","Helstan, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Madam Bluett wurde um 1125 in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Richard Bluett mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1125–Deceased":"about 1125–Desede","1121–Male":"1121–Desede","1147–Female":"1147–Desede","1125–Female":"1125–Desede","1125":"1125","1147":"1147","1121":"1121","Abt 1125"